</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A618FEC9D829" blockId="39.[159,292,545,568]" box="[159,292,545,568]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A618FEC9D829" box="[159,292,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A669FE21D895" blockId="39.[159,775,592,644]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A669FF0ED874" box="[159,227,592,613]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Head.</emphasis>
Chaetosemata elongated, conspicuous. Antenna of male bipectinate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A6A4FE0ED8C0" blockId="39.[159,775,668,721]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A6A4FF0ED8A3" box="[159,227,669,690]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Wings</emphasis>
(Fig. 39). Grey brown. Termen, particularly of hindwing, weakly scalloped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A6D0FD56D8EE" blockId="39.[159,699,745,767]" box="[159,699,745,767]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A6D0FEA8D8EF" box="[159,325,745,766]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1363C7B31E38FF85FECFA6D0FE5BD8EE" box="[341,438,745,767]" captionStart="Figures 159–164" captionStartId="37.[159,249,2002,2023]" captionTargetBox="[160,1440,213,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-14@37.[160,1440,195,1968]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Figures 159–164. Macaria and Boarmioides species: 159, M. abydata, ♂ genitalia; 160, M. abydata, sternum A8 of ♂; 161, M. flavida, ♂ genitalia; 162, M. flavida, sternum A8 of ♂; 163, B. colpias, ♂ genitalia; 164, B. colpias, sternum A8 of ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434198/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Fig. 163</figureCitation>
). Uncus horns absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A72EFCE5D95D" blockId="39.[159,776,791,844]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A72EFE04D93D" box="[159,489,791,812]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Pregenital abdomen of male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1363C7B31E38FF85FE67A72EFD8DD93C" box="[509,608,791,813]" captionStart="Figures 159–164" captionStartId="37.[159,249,2002,2023]" captionTargetBox="[160,1440,213,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-14@37.[160,1440,195,1968]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Figures 159–164. Macaria and Boarmioides species: 159, M. abydata, ♂ genitalia; 160, M. abydata, sternum A8 of ♂; 161, M. flavida, ♂ genitalia; 162, M. flavida, sternum A8 of ♂; 163, B. colpias, ♂ genitalia; 164, B. colpias, sternum A8 of ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434198/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Fig. 164</figureCitation>
). Sternum A8 with a small notch-like emargination; not deeply cleft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A75DFF1FD9E5" blockId="39.[159,775,868,1012]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A75DFE82D968" box="[159,367,868,889]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sterigma well-sclerotized. 
<collectingRegion id="499C15D41E38FF85FD58A75DFCEAD968" box="[706,775,868,889]" country="Turkey" name="Bursa" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Bursa</collectingRegion>
copulatrix: antrum prominent, leading into indistinguishable ductus bursae/corpus bursae of which the ‘first’ (i.e. posterior) half is sclerotized; signum absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A034FE08DE4E" blockId="39.[159,775,1036,1120]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A034FEFADE33" box="[159,279,1037,1058]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E38FF85FE66A034FDB1DE33" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1826" box="[508,604,1037,1058]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Macaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FE66A034FDB1DE33" box="[508,604,1037,1058]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Macaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of horns on the uncus and by the notched, rather than cleft, margin of sternum A8.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A041FE4FDE9C" blockId="39.[159,418,1144,1165]" box="[159,418,1144,1165]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A041FEDFDE9C" box="[159,306,1144,1165]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F34F9BA61E38FF85FEA7A041FE73DE9C" box="[317,414,1144,1165]" name="Morocco" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Morocco</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A09FFE46DF44" blockId="39.[159,775,1190,1365]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A09FFEF3DEAA" box="[159,286,1190,1211]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Comments.</emphasis>
The shape of the valve is similar to that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E38FF85FF5AA0FCFECDDECB" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1826" box="[192,288,1221,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Macaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF5AA0FCFECDDECB" box="[192,288,1221,1242]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Macaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we are reluctant to synonymize the genus because of the absence of uncus horns and the presence of a notched rather than a cleft sternum A 
<quantity id="4CA076D31E38FF85FD66A13BFF5BDF27" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="39" pageNumber="296" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
the male. The taxonomic position of this monotypic genus remains unclear.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E38FF85FF05A154FE5EDF93" blockId="39.[159,435,1389,1411]" box="[159,435,1389,1411]" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E38FF85FF05A154FE98DF92" box="[159,373,1389,1411]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="296">Number of species.</emphasis>
One.
</paragraph>
